  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nAfter custom bootnode created if to open it you see it's name and enode address and `Delete` button which works fine. \r\nHowever after relogin there is nothing from that when opening custom bootnode. Thus there is no option to delete custom bootnode after app restart. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCustom bootnode settings are present\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![dddwd38388d3d](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/90005083-5f991480-dc9f-11ea-8aef-dede4b1482e3.gif)\r\n\r\nCustom bootnode settings are absent after app restart\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account \r\n- Open `Profile` -> `Advanced` -> `Bootnodes` -> `+` (add new bootnode)\r\n- Specify valid name and bootnode address (e.g. `enode://a8a97f126f5e3a340cb4db28a1187c325290ec08b2c9a6b1f19845ac86c46f9fac2ba13328822590fd3de3acb09cc38b5a05272e583a2365ad1fa67f66c55b34@167.99.210.203:30404`)\r\n- Hit `Save`\r\n- Open custom bootnode created\r\n**Actual=Expected result:** Name, address and Delete button are present.\r\n- Restart the app and login to account\r\n- Open custom bootnode created again\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: release1.5/develop\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
